-- Bangkok Bank, Thanachart Capital, Ticon: Thailand Equity Preview
-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 2012-04-23T02:18:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-23/bangkok-bank-thanachart-capital-ticon-thailand-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in  Thailand   trading.  Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close on April 20.  The  SET Index (SET)  rose 0.8 percent to 1,194.60.  Bangkok Bank Pcl (BBL)  : Thailand’s biggest lender said
first-quarter profit rose 25 percent to 8.08 billion baht ($261
million) as companies sought loans to rebuild after last year’s
flooding. That compared with the 7.79 billion-baht average of
six analyst estimates compiled by Bloomberg. Bangkok Bank
climbed 0.5 percent to 193 baht.  Thanachart Capital Pcl (TCAP TB): Prudential Plc is
considering bidding for the insurance business of Thailand’s
Thanachart, Reuters reported, citing people it didn’t identify.
The deal would be worth “around $500 million,” the report
said. Thanachart declined 1.6 percent to 31.25 baht.  Ticon Industrial Connection Pcl (TICON)  : The company
established a subsidiary, Ticon Property Inc., to explore
investment opportunities in real estate in the U.S., it said in
a regulatory filing. Ticon fell 0.8 percent to 12.7 baht.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
